This paper deals with off-policy policy evaluation, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning (RL). RL is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) that deals with decision-making in an uncertain environment. The paper proposes a new method for off-policy policy evaluation that uses options, which are policies over temporally extended actions. This falls under the category of RL and AI. The paper also discusses the use of covariance testing, which is a statistical method used in many areas of computer science, including machine learning and data science. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.DS. Finally, the paper deals with optimization and decision-making, which are topics that fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG).
